      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: cap sessions history and compact session status",
        "body": "Spec #241 upstream source integration.\n\n- Adds config-backed limits for sessions_history includeTools replay\n- Adds compact/full session_status details mode\n- Updates schema/help/labels/docs/tests\n- Rebases onto current upstream main and fixes two unrelated CI hygiene failures in extension code\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Iggy was reachable but session context grew too quickly because `sessions_history includeTools:true` could replay large tool results and `session_status` duplicated full status text in `details.statusText`. This patch caps tool-inclusive history, summarizes tool results, and makes `session_status` compact by default with an explicit full-details opt-in.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Juan's local OpenClaw setup on macOS, 2026-06-06 ET. Installed runtime stayed on OpenClaw `2026.6.1`; this PR was validated in the upstream source clone before installing it into the local runtime, to avoid another local-only runtime patch.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran live OpenClaw/Iggy reachability probes against the real local setup, then validated the source branch with the focused sessions/status tests, prod/test typechecks, lint, extension boundary checks, formatting, and whitespace checks.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Live output from the real local setup:\n\n```console\n$ openclaw gateway status --json | jq '{loaded:.service.loaded,runtime:.service.runtime.status,rpc:.rpc.ok,version:.gateway.version,pluginDrifts:(.pluginVersionDrift.drifts|length)}'\n{\n  \"loaded\": true,\n  \"runtime\": \"running\",\n  \"rpc\": true,\n  \"version\": \"2026.6.1\",\n  \"pluginDrifts\": 0\n}\n\n$ curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:3333/api/debug | jq '{gatewayConnected,pendingRequests,activeTurns,version:.gateway.version}'\n{\n  \"gatewayConnected\": true,\n  \"pendingRequests\": 0,\n  \"activeTurns\": null,\n  \"version\": null\n}\n\n$ curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:3333/api/sessions | jq '{count:length, busy:([.[]? | select(.busy == true)] | length), withPending:([.[]? | select(.pendingChatRunId != null)] | length)}'\n{\n  \"count\": 17,\n  \"busy\": 0,\n  \"withPending\": 0\n}\n\n$ curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:18789/ | head -c 80\n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n```\n\nSource branch validation output:\n\n```console\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/tools/sessions-history-tool.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.sessions.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.session-status.test.ts src/config/config.tools-alsoAllow.test.ts\n4 test files, 104 tests passed across 2 shards\n\n$ pnpm tsgo:prod\npass\n\n$ pnpm tsgo:test\npass\n\n$ pnpm lint:core\npass\n\n$ pnpm run lint:extensions:bundled\npass\n\n$ pnpm run test:extensions:package-boundary:compile\nextension package boundary check passed; compiled plugins: 114\n\n$ pnpm run test:extensions:package-boundary:canary\nextension package boundary check passed; canary plugins: 2\n\n$ pnpm exec oxfmt --check docs/gateway/config-tools.md docs/concepts/session-tool.md src/agents/tools/sessions-history-tool.ts src/agents/tools/session-status-tool.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.sessions.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.session-status.test.ts src/config/types.tools.ts src/config/zod-schema.agent-runtime.ts src/config/schema.help.ts src/config/schema.labels.ts src/config/config.tools-alsoAllow.test.ts extensions/acpx/doctor-contract-api.ts extensions/device-pair/notify.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n\n$ git diff --check\npass\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The real local gateway/Iggy setup was reachable and drained (`gatewayConnected=true`, `pendingRequests=0`, `busy=0`, `withPending=0`) while the source branch now enforces the durable context-bloat controls in upstream code instead of relying on a local runtime patch.\n\n**What was not tested:** The PR branch was not installed into Juan's live OpenClaw runtime. That was intentionally avoided until upstream review/merge so the local setup can return to vanilla and avoid drift.\n\nKnown CI note: local `pnpm check:architecture` still reports an existing madge cycle through agents/channels/config on current upstream main. That failure is outside the Spec #241 context-limit patch and was not introduced by these changed files.\n",
